```rust
fn convert_slice<T, U>(input: &[T]) -> Result<Vec<U>, String>
where
    T: Sized,
    U: Sized,
{
    let input_size = std::mem::size_of::<T>();
    let output_size = std::mem::size_of::<U>();

    if input_size % output_size != 0 || (input_size == 0) != (output_size == 0) {
        return Err("Invalid conversion".to_string());
    }

    let input_len = input.len();
    let output_len = input_len * input_size / output_size;

    if output_len * output_size != input_len * input_size {
        return Err("Invalid conversion".to_string());
    }

    let input_ptr = input.as_ptr() as *const U;
    let output_slice = unsafe { std::slice::from_raw_parts(input_ptr, output_len) };

    Ok(output_slice.to_vec())
}
```

This solution first checks if the size of the input and output types are compatible for conversion. If not, it returns an error. Then, it calculates the length of the output slice and performs the conversion using pointer manipulation. If the conversion is valid, it returns the converted slice; otherwise, it returns an error.

