function requestMulti(array $requests, callable $onEachResponse, callable $onEachError) {
    $responses = [];
    $errors = [];

    // Helper function to check if all requests are completed
    $checkAllRequestsCompleted = function () use (&$responses, &$errors, $onEachResponse, $onEachError) {
        if (count($responses) + count($errors) === count($requests)) {
            foreach ($responses as $response) {
                $onEachResponse($response);
            }
            foreach ($errors as $error) {
                $onEachError($error);
            }
        }
    };

    foreach ($requests as $index => $request) {
        // Make asynchronous request
        makeAsyncRequest($request)
            ->then(function ($response) use (&$responses, $checkAllRequestsCompleted, $index) {
                $responses[$index] = $response;
                $checkAllRequestsCompleted();
            })
            ->catch(function ($error) use (&$errors, $checkAllRequestsCompleted, $index) {
                $errors[$index] = $error;
                $checkAllRequestsCompleted();
            });
    }
}

// Example usage
$requestUrls = ['https://api.example.com/resource1', 'https://api.example.com/resource2'];
$requestMulti(
    $requestUrls,
    function ($response) {
        echo "Received response: " . $response . "\n";
    },
    function ($error) {
        echo "Received error: " . $error . "\n";
    }
);
```

In the solution, the `requestMulti` function iterates through the array of requests and makes asynchronous requests using a hypothetical `makeAsyncRequest` function. It uses Promises or asynchronous functions to handle the asynchronous nature of the requests. For each request, it attaches a `then` callback for successful responses and a `catch` callback for errors. As each request is completed, it updates the `$responses` or `$errors` array and checks if all requests are completed using the helper function `$checkAllRequestsCompleted`. Once all requests are completed, it executes the appropriate callback for each response or error.

